Explanation:
- The handler is defined with @admin_api.route("/users") in app/api/cms/admin.py. admin_api is registered into the "cms" blueprint with url_prefix="/admin" (app/api/cms/__init__.py). That "cms" blueprint itself is registered on the application with url_prefix="/cms" (app/__init__.py). Combining these prefixes gives the full path /cms/admin/users.
- The route decorator in the source does not supply a methods argument, and the function is clearly the "get_admin_users" GET handler; therefore GET is accepted (True).
- The source code does not explicitly declare acceptance of HEAD, POST, OPTIONS, TRACE, PUT, DELETE, PATCH, nor does it include any decorators or method lists that would indicate "all methods" are allowed. Per the instruction to base answers on the code (not on framework runtime behavior), those methods are marked as not acceptable (False), and all_methods is False.
